			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HYPOKALIEMIE</LocID>										<Text>Hypokalemia</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HYPOKALIEMIE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>							<Text>Hypokalemia is a low level of potassium (K+) in the blood serum.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HYPERKALIEMIE</LocID>									<Text>Hyperkalemia</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HYPERKALIEMIE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>						<Text>Hyperkalemia is an elevated level of potassium (K+) in the blood.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_OAP</LocID>												<Text>Pulmonary edema</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_OAP_DESCRIPTION</LocID>									<Text>Pulmonary edema is fluid accumulation in the tissue and air spaces of the lungs.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_ABOLITION_POULS</LocID>									<Text>No pulse</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_ABOLITION_POULS_DESCRIPTION</LocID>						<Text>There is no perceived pulse to a member.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_MARBRURE</LocID>											<Text>Livedo reticularis</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_MARBRURE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>								<Text>Livedo reticularis is a common skin finding consisting of a mottled reticulated vascular pattern that appears as a lace-like purplish discoloration of the skin. The discoloration is caused by swelling of the venules owing to obstruction of capillaries by small blood clots.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_POUL_HYPERPULSE</LocID>									<Text>Hyperpulsatile pulse</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_POUL_HYPERPULSE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>						<Text>Pulp hyperpulsatility</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_TURJESCENCE_JUGULAIRE</LocID>							<Text>JVD</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_TURJESCENCE_JUGULAIRE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>				<Text>Jugular vein distention (JVD) occurs when the pressure inside the vena cava increases and appears as a bulge running down the right side of a person’s neck.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_REFLUX_HJ</LocID>										<Text>AJR</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_REFLUX_HJ_DESCRIPTION</LocID>							<Text>The abdominojugular reflux (AJR) sign is useful in diagnosing right ventricular failure, but is often performed and interpreted incorrectly.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HEPATALGIE</LocID>										<Text>Hepatalgia</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HEPATALGIE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>							<Text>A painful liver.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_SOUFFLE_ABDOMINAL</LocID>								<Text>Abdominal murmur</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_SOUFFLE_ABDOMINAL_DESCRIPTION</LocID>					<Text>The presence of an abdominal murmur may reflect the existence of an aneurysm of the abdominal aorta or a narrowing of the renal arteries.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_SOUFFLE_VASCULAIRE</LocID>								<Text>Vascular murmur</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_SOUFFLE_VASCULAIRE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>					<Text></Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
+++ v0.02 +++
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_MACROGLOSSIA</LocID>											<Text>Macroglossia</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_MACROGLOSSIA_DESCRIPTION</LocID>								<Text>Abnormal increase in tongue volume.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HYPOGLYCEMIA</LocID>											<Text>Hypoglycemia</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HYPOGLYCEMIA_DESCRIPTION</LocID>								<Text>Low blood glucose.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_GYNECOMASTIA</LocID>											<Text>Gynecomastia</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_GYNECOMASTIA_DESCRIPTION</LocID>								<Text>Abnormal increase in breast volume in men.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_ATROPHIE_TESTICULE</LocID>									<Text>Testicular atrophy</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_ATROPHIE_TESTICULE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>						<Text>Decrease in testicle size.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_DRY_SKIN</LocID>												<Text>Xerosis</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_DRY_SKIN_DESCRIPTION</LocID>									<Text>Dry skin is skin that has lost its protective fatty layer and becomes dehydrated.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HYPERPRL</LocID>												<Text>Hyperprolactinemia</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HYPERPRL_DESCRIPTION</LocID>									<Text>Abnormal increase in plasma prolactin concentration.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_INSUFFISANCE_SR_AIGUE</LocID>								<Text>Acute adrenal insufficiency</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_INSUFFISANCE_SR_AIGUE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>					<Text>A primary adrenal insufficiency caused by a sudden defective production of adrenal steroids.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HYPOCALCEMIA</LocID>											<Text>Hypocalcemia</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HYPOCALCEMIA_DESCRIPTION</LocID>								<Text>Hypocalcemia is an abnormal drop in the level of calcium in the blood.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_THROMBOCYTOSE</LocID>										<Text>Thrombocytosis</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_THROMBOCYTOSE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>							<Text>Thrombocytosis is a condition in which there is an excessive number of platelets in the blood.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
+++ v0.03 +++
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_GALLSTONES</LocID>										<Text>GALLSTONES</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HTAP</LocID>												<Text>Pulmonary hypertension</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HEMOLYSE</LocID>											<Text>HEMOLYSE</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_MED_APLASIA</LocID>										<Text>Bone aplasia</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_MED_APLASIA_DESCRIPTION</LocID>							<Text>Bone marrow aplasia refers to those hematologic conditions that are caused by a marked reduction and/or defect in the pluripotent or committed stem cells, or the failure of the bone marrow microenvironment to support hematopoiesis.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
+++ v0.03.2 +++
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HEPATITIS</LocID>									<Text>Hepatitis</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HEPATITIS_DESCRIPTION</LocID>						<Text>Liver inflammation.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_TELANGIECTASIS</LocID>								<Text>Telangiectasia</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_TELANGIECTASIS_DESCRIPTION</LocID>					<Text>Telangiectasias, also known as spider veins, are small dilated blood vessels that can occur near the surface of the skin or mucous membranes, measuring between 0.5 and 1 millimeter in diameter. These dilated blood vessels can develop anywhere on the body but are commonly seen on the face around the nose, cheeks and chin.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_SURCHARGE_FER</LocID>								<Text>Iron overload</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_SURCHARGE_FER_DESCRIPTION</LocID>					<Text>Iron overload or hemochromatosis indicates accumulation of iron in the body from any cause.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
+++ v0.03.3 +++
