			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_REJET_GREFFE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>						<Text>The patient is in the process of rejection of his transplant, which corresponds to the destruction of the graft transplanted into an organism, due to an immune response directed against him.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HEMORRAGIE_DIG_HAUTE</LocID>							<Text>UDH</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HEMORRAGIE_DIG_HAUTE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>				<Text>During an upper digestive hemorrhage (UDH), the bleeding occurs upstream of the Treitz ligament (oesophagus, stomach and duodenum).</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HEMORRAGIE_DIG_BASSE</LocID>							<Text>LDH</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_CRP_HEMORRAGIE_DIG_BASSE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>				<Text>In a lower digestive hemorrhage (LDH), blood loss originates downstream from the Treitz ligament (small intestine, colon, rectum and anus).</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
-->	
			
			
