			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ISCHEMIE_MS</LocID>											<Text>Upper limb tissue ischemia</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ISCHEMIE_MS_DESCRIPTION</LocID>								<Text>Ischemia is the cessation or insufficiency of blood circulation in a part of the body or an organ, which deprives the cells of oxygen supply and causes their necrosis. Ischemia can be due to blockage of a vessel (thrombosis) or compression of an artery (stenosis).</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ISCHEMIE_MI</LocID>											<Text>Lower limb tissue ischemia</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ISCHEMIE_MI_DESCRIPTION</LocID>								<Text>Ischemia is the cessation or insufficiency of blood circulation in a part of the body or an organ, which deprives the cells of oxygen supply and causes their necrosis. Ischemia can be due to blockage of a vessel (thrombosis) or compression of an artery (stenosis).</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
