			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ADENOME_CORTICOTROPE_F</LocID>						<Text>Corticotropic adenoma</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ADENOME_CORTICOTROPE_H</LocID>						<Text>Corticotropic adenoma</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ADENOME_CORTICOTROPE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>				<Text>The test is in favor of the diagnosis of non-curable hypercortisolism if the cortisolemia does not drop below the threshold of 18 ng / ml [50 nmol / l]</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ADENOME_THYREOTROPE</LocID>							<Text>Thyrotropic adenoma</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ADENOME_THYREOTROPE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>				<Text>Discovery of central hyperthyroidism at the blood test. This is characterized by a high concentration of thyroid hormones associated with a normal high or abnormal concentration of TSH.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_PAN_HYPOPITUITARISME_F</LocID>						<Text>Panhypopituitarism</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
