			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_PAN_HYPOPITUITARISME_DESCRIPTION</LocID>				<Text>Discovery of a pituitary adenoma that prevents the proper functioning of the pineal gland on MRI.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ISRNP_F</LocID>										<Text>Peripheral adrenal insufficiency</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ISRNP_H</LocID>										<Text>Peripheral adrenal insufficiency</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ISRNP_DESCRIPTION</LocID>								<Text>Discovery of peripheral adrenal insufficiency during the Synacthene test. This is characterized by a low cortisol level associated with a high concentration of ACTH.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_21OH_F</LocID>										<Text>21-OH deficiency</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_21OH_H</LocID>										<Text>21-OH deficiency</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_21OH_DESCRIPTION</LocID>								<Text>It is accepted by the entire endocrinologist community that the diagnosis of D21OH-NC is based on the dosage of 17OHP in the morning and at best in the first part of the cycle. The sample must be taken in the absence of or at a distance from treatment with glucocorticoids, since even "substitute" treatment and a fortiori pharmacological treatment introduces a risk of ignoring the diagnosis (false negative) by inhibiting the corticotropic axis. The sampling for the determination of 17OHP must also be done in the morning, because if it is done in the afternoon, the concentration of 17OHP can be found within the normal range in a patient with D21OH-NC simply because of fluctuations nycthemeral of adrenal cortical function.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ISF_CORTICOT</LocID>									<Text>Central adrenal insufficiency</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ISF_CORTICOT_DESCRIPTION</LocID>						<Text>Discovery of central adrenal insufficiency during the Synacthene test. This is characterized by low cortisol levels associated with a low or abnormally normal concentration of ACTH.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_AC_ANTI_CASR</LocID>									<Text>Anti-CASR Ab</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
