			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_DEFICIT_AIIB_B3_DESCRIPTION</LocID>			<Text>Quantitative and / or qualitative anomalies of the integrin alphaIIb beta3 are found.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MUTATION_RP</LocID>							<Text>RP Mutations</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MUTATION_RP_DESCRIPTION</LocID>				<Text>Ribosomal proteins (RPs) from either the small (RPS7, RPS17, RPS19, RPS24) or the large (RPL5, RPL11, RPL35a) ribosomal subunit are mutated.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_GLUCOCEREBROSIDASE</LocID>					<Text>Glucocerebrosidase deficiency</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_GLUCOCEREBROSIDASE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>		<Text>Low glucocerebrosidase level leading to accumulation of glucosylceramide deposits.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MUTATION_SH2D1A</LocID>						<Text>SH2D1A mutation </Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MUTATION_SH2D1A_DESCRIPTION</LocID>			<Text>Mutation of the SH2D1A gene which is located on the X chromosome. This gene codes for a protein called SAP (signalling lymphocyte activation molecular [SLAM] associated protein).</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_SIDEROBLASTE</LocID>							<Text>Sideroblast</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_SIDEROBLASTE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>				<Text>Sideroblasts have been found. These are iron-containing granulations stained with Perls's reagent, corresponding to aggregates of ribosomes and ferritin.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ERYTHROBLASTOPENIE</LocID>					<Text>Erythroblast</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ERYTHROBLASTOPENIE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>		<Text>Low erythroblast rate.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_HÉMOGLOBINE_C</LocID>							<Text>Hemoglobin  C</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_HÉMOGLOBINE_C_DESCRIPTION</LocID>				<Text>Discovery of hemoglobins type C with a blood smear.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_HÉMOGLOBINE_D</LocID>							<Text>Hemoglobin  D</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_HÉMOGLOBINE_D_DESCRIPTION</LocID>				<Text>Discovery of hemoglobins type D with a blood smear.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_HÉMOGLOBINE_E</LocID>							<Text>Hemoglobin  E</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_HÉMOGLOBINE_E_DESCRIPTION</LocID>				<Text>Discovery of hemoglobins type E with a blood smear.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_HÉMOGLOBINE_M</LocID>							<Text>Hemoglobin  M</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_HÉMOGLOBINE_M_DESCRIPTION</LocID>				<Text>Discovery of hemoglobins type M with a blood smear.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_TRIADE_PLUMMER_VINSON</LocID>					<Text>Triad</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_TRIADE_PLUMMER_VINSON_DESCRIPTION</LocID>		<Text>Classical triad of dysphagia, iron-deficiency anemia and esophageal webs.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MUTATION_ACVRL_ENG</LocID>					<Text>Mutation</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MUTATION_ACVRL_ENG_DESCRIPTION</LocID>		<Text>A mutation in one of the two ACVRL or ENG genes involved in the TGF-beta signaling pathway has been found.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_LT_ANORMAL</LocID>							<Text>Coombs +</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_LT_ANORMAL_DESCRIPTION</LocID>				<Text>The Coombs test is positive.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MUTATION_HFE</LocID>								<Text>HFE mutation</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MUTATION_HFE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>					<Text>The HFE gene located on chromosome 6 is mutated. Two types of alterations exist: the C282Y mutation and the H63D mutation.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MUTATION_HJV_OU_HAMP</LocID>						<Text>Mutation</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MUTATION_HJV_OU_HAMP_DESCRIPTION</LocID>			<Text>Mutations in the gene coding for hemojuvelin (HJV) on chromosome 1 or mutations in the gene coding for hepcidin (HAMP) on chromosome 19 have been found.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MUTATION_TFR2</LocID>								<Text>TFR2 mutation</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MUTATION_TFR2_DESCRIPTION</LocID>					<Text>Mutations in the transferrin receptor-2 (TFR2) gene on chromosome 7 have been found.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MUTATION_SLC40A1</LocID>							<Text>SLC40A1 mutation</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MUTATION_SLC40A1_DESCRIPTION</LocID>				<Text>Mutations in the SLC40A1 gene located on chromosome 2 which codes for ferroportin (FPN) have been found.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MO_HYPOCELLULAIRE</LocID>						<Text>Hypocellular bone marrow</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_MO_HYPOCELLULAIRE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>			<Text>The bone marrow is hypocellular, it's "empty".</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>

			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_PURPURA_THROMBOPENIQUE</LocID>				<Text>Thrombocytopenic purpura</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_PURPURA_THROMBOPENIQUE_DESCRIPTION</LocID>	<Text>Symptoms suggestive of thrombocytopenic purpura.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_DRESS_SD</LocID>								<Text>DRESS</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_DRESS_SD_DESCRIPTION</LocID>					<Text>Symptoms suggestive of DRESS syndrome.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ANTICORPS_ANTI_F4P</LocID>					<Text>Anti-PF4 ab</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
			<GameDBLocalizedString>	<LocID>SYM_MOREDG_ANTICORPS_ANTI_F4P_DESCRIPTION</LocID>		<Text>Anti-PF4 / heparin antibodies were detected by ELISA.</Text>	</GameDBLocalizedString>
